5 Subject: Elections; nominations; write-in candidates; failure of a major
6 political party to nominate a candidate by primary
7 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to require that a
8 write-in candidate must receive at least the same number of votes as the
9 number of signatures required for the office in order to qualify as the winner in
10 a primary election unless that write-in candidate receives more votes than any
11 other candidate whose name is printed on the ballot. This bill also prohibits a
12 major political party from nominating a candidate for a general election party
13 if that party failed to nominate a candidate during the primary election.
14 An act relating to the number of votes required for a write-in candidate to
15 win a primary election
16 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
17 * * * Write-In Candidates Thresholds for Primary Elections * * *
18 Sec. 1. 17 V.S.A. § 2370 is amended to read:
19 § 2370. WRITE-IN CANDIDATES
