1 (a) A write-in candidate shall not qualify as a primary winner unless he or
2 she the candidate receives at least one-half the same number of votes as the
3 number of signatures required for his or her the candidate’s office on a primary
4 petition, except that if a write-in candidate receives more votes than a any
5 other candidate whose name is printed on the ballot, he or she the write-in
6 candidate may qualify as a primary winner.
7 (b) The write-in candidate who qualifies as a primary winner under this
8 section must still be determined a winner under section 2369 of this chapter
9 before he or she the candidate becomes the party’s candidate in the general
10 election.
